      <hedline>
        <hl1>Olympic Talk Show</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Glenn Osborn letter on September 20 article holds NBC has turned Olympics into talk show</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Sports Editor:</p>
        <p>If NBC wants to know why its ratings are so low for the Olympics (''NBC's Ratings for the Olympics Are Worst Ever,'' The Times, Sept. 20), look to its own bloated programming. Their loquacious hosts and human interest stories have turned the Games into a talk show. The Olympic coverage in The Times indicates dozens of events that NBC has passed on in favor of time spent on talk, analysis and just plain yakking.</p>
        <p>GLENN OSBORN  Perrysburg, Ohio</p>
      </block>
